Tom already dried 10 pairs of socks successfully in 10 hours. To find out how long it would take him to dry 7 pairs, we need to consider that the drying time is not proportional to the number of socks, but rather a constant factor.

Since each pair took 10 hours to dry and he has already proven this method effective, we can assume that drying 7 pairs will also take 10 hours. 

Therefore, it would take Tom 10 hours to dry seven pairs of socks under the same weather conditions.
